  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7 and boil a kettle</p><p>Add your <strong>tortiglioni</strong> to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> with a large pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat and cook for an initial 4-5 min</p><p>Reboil half a kettle</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/cheesy-broccoli-pasta-bake/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, chop your <strong>leek[s]</strong> in half lengthways, wash thoroughly to remove any grit then top, tail and slice finely</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your<strong> garlic</strong></p><p>Grate your <strong>cheddar cheese</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/cheesy-broccoli-pasta-bake/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>After an initial 4-5 min, add your <strong>Tenderstem broccoli</strong> to the tortiglioni<strong> </strong>and cook for a further 3-4 min or until everything is cooked with a slight bite</p><p>Once cooked, drain and return to the pot</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/cheesy-broccoli-pasta-bake/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with 20g <span class=\"text-purple\">[30g]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [40g] </span><strong>butter </strong>over a medium heat</p><p>Once the butter has melted, add the <strong>sliced leek[s]</strong> and cook for 5-6 min or until softened, then add the <strong>chopped garlic</strong> and cook for a further 1 min</p><p>Dissolve your <strong>vegetable stock mix </strong>in 100ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[150ml]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [200ml] </span><strong>boiled water </strong>and add 250ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[375ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[500ml]</span><strong> milk </strong>– this is your<strong> creamy stock</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/cheesy-broccoli-pasta-bake/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [2 tbsp]</span><strong> flour</strong> to the pan and stir with a wooden spoon for 1-2 min</p><p>Gradually whisk in the <strong>creamy stock</strong> and cook for 5 min or until a smooth, thick sauce remains</p><p>Once thick, stir through the <strong>grated cheddar cheese</strong>, <strong>half</strong> your <strong>grated Italian hard cheese</strong> (save the rest for later!) and your <strong>Dijon mustard</strong> (not a mustard fan? Go easy!) – this is your<strong> cheese sauce</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/cheesy-broccoli-pasta-bake/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Combine the <strong>remaining grated Italian hard cheese</strong> with your <strong>panko breadcrumbs</strong>, <strong>pumpkin seeds</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> – these are your <strong>cheesy breadcrumbs</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>drained tortiglioni & Tenderstem</strong> to the<strong> </strong>cheese<strong> </strong>sauce and stir it all together</p><p>Transfer to an<strong> oven-proof dish</strong> and top with the <strong>cheesy breadcrumbs</strong></p><p>Put the dish in the oven for 10-15 min or until golden and bubbling</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/cheesy-broccoli-pasta-bake/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, combine your <strong>cider vinegar</strong> with 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> in a large bowl – this is your<strong> dressing</strong></p><p>Wash your<strong> salad</strong>, then pat it dry with kitchen paper</p><p>Add the <strong>salad</strong> to the dressing and gently mix together – this is your <strong>dressed salad</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/cheesy-broccoli-pasta-bake/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once done, remove the dish from the oven and leave to stand for a few min before serving (this helps the flavours to develop and makes it easier to serve!) – this is your <strong>cheesy broccoli pasta bake</strong></p><p>Serve with the <strong>dressed salad</strong> to the side</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
